parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS controller can cause the loss of anti-lock braking, traction control, and speedometer functionality, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: ABS and ASC warning lights illuminate
speedometer stops working
odometer freezes
fuel gauge becomes inoperative
automatic steering control is lost
and ABS protection is disabled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power brake booster can cause the loss of power-assisted braking, leading to increased stopping distances and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to stop properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the ABS braking light to appear on the dashboard, leading to confusion and potential accidents.
symptoms: The ABS braking light appears on the dashboard and remains on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of Takata airbags can lead to unexpected deployment, causing injuries or fatalities, or failure to deploy in the event of an accident, leaving occupants vulnerable to harm.
symptoms: Airbag light on the dashboard turns on
airbag deploys without warning or impact
airbag fails to deploy in an accident
injuries or fatalities occur due to airbag malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, distractions, or loss of control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Airbag deploys without warning or impact
airbag deploys while driving at high speeds
airbag deploys without any apparent reason.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident can lead to injuries or fatalities, as occupants are left unprotected.
symptoms: Airbag fails to deploy in an accident
injuries or fatalities occur due to airbag malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is unable to be controlled or stopped.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates forward
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck
the vehicle lurches forward when at a stop
the engine surges when cold in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic control unit can disable critical safety features, such as anti-lock brakes, stability control, and alarm systems, making the vehicle unsafe to drive.
symptoms: The odometer
speedometer
cruise control
automatic door locks
and alarm are disabled
the anti-lock brakes and stability control are disabled
the vehicle cannot be locked to prevent intruders.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dislodgement of the accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes dislodged
causing the accelerator to get stuck
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly.
